	/**
	 * upcoming_feature: Ability to easily create your own REST Message/method records and call
	 *  them from Integration Core without trying to figure out authentication and basic stuff
	 *  like that.
	 *
	 * @description NOTE: THIS METHOD HAS BEEN DEPRECATED, in favor of ._getRESTObject() and
	 *  ._executeRESTCall().
	 *
	 * Do a simple REST call to Tanium.
	 *
	 * NOTE: Your REST Method MUST have a string parameter called "session_id" which sets the value
	 *  of a header in your REST Method called "session".
	 * Also, if you haven't hard-coded the full API URL in your REST Method and are using string
	 *  parameters to specify the API base URL (which IS recommended), make sure to specify that
	 *  string parameter in the stringParameters argument object.
	 *
	 * @param {string} restMessageName - The name of the REST Message to use, not including the
	 *  scope prefix.
	 * Example: "Tanium Integration Core".
	 *
	 * @param {string} restMethodName - The name of the REST Method to use.
	 * Example: "System status"
	 *
	 * @param {{string_param_name : string}} [stringParameters={}] - OPTIONAL: An object containing
	 *  any string parameters you'd like to have specified OTHER than the default ones.
	 * Default string parameters are:
	 *  -session_id: Set to the current session ID or API token depending on how the core app is
	 *   configured.
	 *
	 * @param {object} [requestBodyOverride={}] - OPTIONAL: A request body to explicitly set,
	 *  overriding any request body that may (or may not) be in the REST Method record specified
	 *  in the restMethodName argument.
	 * You can simply not specify this argument, or you can specifically pass the value "undefined".
	 *
	 *  @param {boolean} [ignoreHttpStatusErrors=false] - If set to true, this method will attempt
	 *   to return something meaningful (hopefully a response body) even if the HTTP status is
	 *   something other than 2XX.
	 *
	 * @private
	 */
	__wip_doAPICallFromMsg: function(
		restMessageName,
		restMethodName,
		stringParameters,
		requestBodyOverride,
		ignoreHttpStatusErrors
	) {
		var strParamName,
			strParamValue,
			rTaniumMsg,
			responseBody;
		//Init: Validate required params
		if (!restMessageName || !restMethodName) {
			gs.error(
				'_doRESTCall() method called but restMessageName or restMethodName not specified. ' +
